<paragraph id="6B3836CFF23AFFA5328C8FC6677642AA" blockId="0.[136,1452,1423,1844]" box="[136,346,1423,1447]" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">
<heading id="307081A3F23AFFA5328C8FC6677642AA" bold="true" box="[136,346,1423,1447]" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" reason="2">
<taxonomicName id="AC874D4CF23AFFA5328C8FC6677642AA" authorityName="Stschegleew" authorityYear="1853" box="[136,346,1423,1447]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kowalenskyi">
<emphasis id="59F3EADDF23AFFA5328C8FC6677642AA" bold="true" box="[136,346,1423,1447]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Silene kowalenskyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6B3836CFF23AFFA5328C8FFD6326403E" blockId="0.[136,1452,1423,1844]" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">
<bibRefCitation id="0F164B3EF23AFFA5328C8FFD67A442C6" author="Eggens, F. &amp; Jafari, F. &amp; Thollesson, M. &amp; Crameri, S. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Oxelman, B." box="[136,392,1459,1484]" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref982" refString="Eggens, F., Jafari, F., Thollesson, M., Crameri, S., Zarre, S. &amp; Oxelman, B. (2020) Phylogeny and species delimitation in Silene sect. Arenosae (Caryophyllaceae): a new section. Phytokeys 159: 1 - 34. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / phytokeys. 159.51500" type="journal article" year="2020">
Eggens 
<emphasis id="59F3EADDF23AFFA532D98FFD673F42C6" box="[221,275,1459,1483]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">et al.</emphasis>
(2020: 16)
</bibRefCitation>
proposed to neotypify the name 
<taxonomicName id="AC874D4CF23AFFA530E38FFA659D42C6" authorityName="Stschegleew" authorityYear="1853" box="[743,945,1459,1483]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kowalenskyi">
<emphasis id="59F3EADDF23AFFA530E38FFA659D42C6" box="[743,945,1459,1483]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Silene kowalenskyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which was regarded as synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="AC874D4CF23AFFA537388FFD676942E2" authority="Koch (1841: 711)" authorityName="Koch" authorityPageNumber="711" authorityYear="1841" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arenosa">
<emphasis id="59F3EADDF23AFFA537388FFD638742C6" box="[1340,1451,1460,1483]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">S. arenosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="0F164B3EF23AFFA5328C8F9E676942E2" author="Koch, K." box="[136,325,1495,1519]" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" pagination="705 - 723" refId="ref1050" refString="Koch, K. (1841) Catalogus Plantarum, quas in itinere per Caucasum, Georgiam, Armeniamque annis MDCCCXXXVI et MDCCCXXXVII. Linnaea 15: 705 - 723." type="journal article" year="1841">Koch (1841: 711)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, using a specimen collected by Kowalensky in 
<collectingCountry id="1390765FF23AFFA531368F9E658B42E2" box="[818,935,1495,1519]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
and deposited at G-BOIS (barcode G00544651). This neotypification should instead be a lectotypification according to Art. 9.19 of 
<emphasis id="59F3EADDF23AFFA531FA8FB2628E411E" box="[1022,1186,1531,1555]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Shenzhen Code</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="0F164B3EF23AFFA536B48FB263AF411E" author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[1200,1411,1531,1555]" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" refId="ref1136" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (Eds.) (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis id="59F3EADDF23AFFA537098FB5636F411E" box="[1293,1347,1531,1555]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). In fact, Stschegleew (l.c.) stated: “j’ai reçu une petite collection des plantes (110 espèces) que Mr. Kowalensky a cueillies entre Nackitschewan et 
<collectingRegion id="A943F82DF23AFFA5334A8C0A67954156" box="[334,441,1603,1627]" country="Azerbaijan" name="Ordubad" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Ordoubad</collectingRegion>
et qu’il a eu la bonté de m’envoyer” (= “I received a small collection of plants (110 species) that Mr. Kowalensky gathered between Nackitschewan and 
<collectingRegion id="A943F82DF23AFFA5310C8C2E655F4172" box="[776,883,1639,1663]" country="Azerbaijan" name="Ordubad" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Ordoubad</collectingRegion>
and that he was kind enough to send me”. Moreover, as reported on page 330, since Stschegleew worked in Moscow, personnel at LE and KW searched for additional specimens and, in addition to the one at G-BOIS cited above, one was located in the Turczaninow Herbarium (KW-TURCZ) at the National Herbarium of 
<collectingCountry id="1390765FF23AFFA5337A8C9A67F841E6" box="[382,468,1747,1771]" name="Ukraine" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
(KW). Both the G-BOIS and KW-TURCZ sheets are part of the original material and eligible as 
<typeStatus id="B43C886DF23AFFA532A18CBE67394002" box="[165,277,1783,1807]" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">lectotypes</typeStatus>
. We here designate the specimen at G-BOIS as the 
<typeStatus id="B43C886DF23AFFA531398CBE65B34002" box="[829,927,1783,1807]" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">lectotype</typeStatus>
since it bears flowers which are important in the taxonomy of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="AC874D4CF23AFFA533868D5267EF403E" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[386,451,1819,1843]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="59F3EADDF23AFFA533868D5267EF403E" box="[386,451,1819,1843]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Silene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The specimen at KW-TURCZ, which includes only fruits, is the isolectotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
